          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-04-05 14:15:25" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(derivative of {L:τελέω&lt;SDBG:τελέω:000004&gt;}[e] ‘to pay taxes,’ {D:57.178}) a place where taxes or revenue was collected from those entering a town to sell produce</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>revenue office</Gloss>
                <Gloss>tax office</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In the ancient world taxes were primarily of two types: (1) a head tax on each individual (which was relatively small) and (2) revenue or tribute paid for goods and produce brought into an area for sale. The latter was essentially a kind of ‘sales tax,’ but paid by the seller who obviously increased the prices of goods accordingly.</Comments>
